    <!-- CHAPTER 1 -->
    <h2>CHAPTER 1: INTRODUCTION</h2>
    <h3>Introduction</h3>
    <p>In today's digital world, everything is becoming automated. Educational institutions like ours often face difficulties in maintaining paper-based attendance registers. It leads to paperwork, calculation errors, and waste of time. The <b>Attendance Management System</b> is a solution to these problems. It allows staff to mark attendance online and students to view their status instantly.</p>
    
    <h3>Objectives of the Project</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>To replace the manual attendance register with a computerized system.</li>
        <li>To calculate attendance percentage automatically to avoid errors.</li>
        <li>To provide separate logins for teachers and students.</li>
        <li>To help students check their exam eligibility status (Eligible/Shortage) easily.</li>
        <li>To save time during class hours.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Scope of the Project</h3>
    <p>The project is currently designed for the Computer Science department. It covers student details, subject allocation, and daily attendance recording. In the future, it can be expanded to the entire college, including SMS alerts to parents for absentees.</p>

    <div class="page-break"></div>

    <!-- CHAPTER 2 -->
    <h2>CHAPTER 2: SYSTEM STUDY</h2>
    <h3>Existing System</h3>
    <p>Currently, the attendance is maintained manually in a green logbook.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Disadvantages:</b></li>
        <ul>
            <li>Teachers have to carry the register to every class.</li>
            <li>Calculating monthly and semester-wise percentage is manual and prone to mistakes.</li>
            <li>Students don't know their current percentage unless the teacher tells them.</li>
            <li>Registers can get damaged or lost.</li>
        </ul>
    </ul>

    <h3>Proposed System</h3>
    <p>The proposed system is a web application where data is stored in a central database.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Advantages:</b></li>
        <ul>
            <li>Attendance can be marked from any computer in the lab or staff room.</li>
            <li>Calculation is automatic and instant.</li>
            <li>Students can login and check their own attendance anytime.</li>
            <li>Data is safe and secure in the MySQL database.</li>
            <li>Reports are generated with a single click.</li>
        </ul>
    </ul>

