    <!-- CHAPTER 4 -->
    <h2>CHAPTER 4: SYSTEM DESIGN</h2>
    <h3>System Architecture</h3>
    <p>The system follows a standard client-server architecture.</p>
    <ol>
        <li><b>Client:</b> The web browser (Chrome/Edge) where the user interacts with the UI.</li>
        <li><b>Server:</b> The Apache server (XAMPP) processes the PHP scripts.</li>
        <li><b>Database:</b> MySQL stores all the user and attendance data.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Entity Relationship Diagram (ER Diagram)</h3>
    <p>The main entities in my project are:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Users:</b> Stores login info for teachers and students.</li>
        <li><b>Students:</b> Links to the user table and stores personal details.</li>
        <li><b>Courses/Subjects:</b> Stores the academic curriculum.</li>
        <li><b>Attendance:</b> Connects students, subjects, and dates.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Data Flow Diagram (DFD)</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>User</b> -> Login -> <b>System</b> -> Validate -> <b>Dashboard</b></li>
        <li><b>Teacher</b> -> Select Class -> Mark Attendance -> <b>Database</b></li>
        <li><b>Student</b> -> Request Status -> <b>System</b> -> Fetch Data -> <b>Show Percentage</b></li>
    </ul>

